--------------------
Preparation and run:
--------------------

1.
Download the automated test framework from GIT, “automationTesting” branch:
https://github.com/dnanexus/precision-fda
The framework is located at: https://github.com/dnanexus/precision-fda/tree/automationTesting/test/functional
It is a Maven project.

2.
Make sure Maven is installed on your machine.

3.
Make sure Java (JRE and JDK) is installed on the machine where you are planning to run the automated suite.
Works fine with “openjdk” ver. 1.8.*

4.
Make sure Firefox is installed on the machine. Works fine with the last version 56.0

Download the “geckodriver” file, save unpacked file to “.../precision-fda/test/functional/drivers” folder.
The file should be downloaded here: https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases

5.
Edit the file “precision-fda/test/functional/src/main/resources/settings.properties” if needed.

6.
Edit the file “precision-fda/test/functional/src/main/resources/application.conf.example”: the file is a container for test users data.
Rename the file “application.conf.example” to “application.conf”.

7.
Make sure VPN is active if needed.

8.
Via command line: go to ""/precision-fda/test/functional/” folder.
Execute “mvn clean test -Dsuite=allSuitesParallel.xml”, where “allSuitesParallel.xml” -
the file with description what test cases should be run and how they should be run.
In our case: all existing test cases in parallel using 3 threads.


----------------------
How to review results:
----------------------

a. “precision-fda/test/functional/target/surefire-reports/html/index.html” - is an html report of the run

b. The folder “precision-fda/test/functional/target/debug-log/” will have full log files and screenshots (if it is enabled in the “properties” file).